-- Claressa Shields of the U.S. Wins Olympic Gold in Women’s Boxing
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-08-09T16:43:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/claressa-shields-of-the-u-s-wins-olympic-gold-in-women-s-boxing.html
Claressa Shields, 17, of the U.S. won
the boxing gold medal in the women’s middleweight division at
the Olympics.  She beat Nadezda Torlopova of  Russia  on points in the final
in London. Women’s boxing is making its debut as an Olympic
sport.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  